# NLP & LLM Rules

## Language Detection
- Arabic: check if text contains Unicode range \u0600-\u06FF (>30% of chars)
- French: check for common French words (le, la, les, de, du, des, et, est, un, une) or accented chars (é, è, ê, à, ç, ù, ô)
- English: default fallback
- Use `franc` npm package as backup for edge cases
- Lebanese content is often mixed: prioritize Arabic detection if any Arabic chars present

## Hugging Face Inference API
- Endpoint: `https://api-inference.huggingface.co/models/{model}`
- Auth: Bearer token from `process.env.HF_API_TOKEN`
- Models:
  - Arabic: `CAMeL-Lab/bert-base-arabic-camelbert-msa-sentiment` → positive/negative/neutral
  - French: `nlptown/bert-base-multilingual-uncased-sentiment` → 1-5 stars (map: 1-2→ombre, 3→neutre, 4-5→lumiere)
  - English: `distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english` → POSITIVE/NEGATIVE
- Batch: send array of texts in one request (max 10 per batch)
- Cache: LRU cache (max 1000 entries, TTL 1 hour)
- Timeout: 5 seconds per request
- Fallback: if HF API fails, use keyword-only classification
- NEVER block the main data pipeline on NLP — run async, update classification when ready

## Classification Ensemble
```
finalScore = (keywordScore × 0.3) + (hfScore × 0.5) + (gdeltTone × 0.2)
```
- If HF unavailable: keywordScore × 0.6 + gdeltTone × 0.4
- If gdeltTone unavailable: keywordScore × 0.4 + hfScore × 0.6
- Confidence = weighted average of individual confidences

## Entity Extraction (lightweight)
- Use regex patterns for Lebanese entities:
  - Politicians: maintain a list of ~50 names (Nabih Berri, Nawaf Salam, etc.)
  - Parties: Hezbollah, Amal, FPM, FL, Kataeb, PSP, etc.
  - Cities: gazetteer from lebanon.ts config
  - Organizations: UNIFIL, LAF, ISF, BDL, etc.
- Map extracted city names to coordinates for geocoding
- No need for a full NER model at this stage

## Cost Management
- HF free tier: ~30k chars/month
- Classify only: titles (not full articles)
- Average title: 60 chars → ~500 classifications/month free
- To extend: cache aggressively, skip classification for sources with built-in tone (GDELT)
- Future: run Transformers.js in browser for zero-cost client-side inference
